subSubSection.paragraph:
Description. Size
: Length 3.0–8.0 mm; width 
1.2–2.2 mm
. Form (
Fig. 121
): Oblong short (about 2X longer than broad) or oblong long (about 4X longer than broad), body not deep. 
Vestiture
: Dorsum profusely vested with white pubescence, antenna moderately setose, elytra with 1° and 2° setae. 
Head
(
Figs. 3–5
, 
13
): Cranium subquadrate, frons wider or narrower than width of eye, profusely indented with small, setiferous punctures; gula (
Figs. 4
, 
15
) large, subquadrate, sutures divergent, gula with 2 welldeveloped, setose post-gular processes (
Fig. 4
); labrum (
Fig. 9
) shallow, incised distally, tormal processes not contiguous, epipharyngeal plate small; mandibles (
Fig. 7
) stout, anterior dens acuminate, medial and posterior dens well-developed, penicillus well-developed; maxilla (
Figs. 6
, 
14
) with laterolacinia absent, terminal palpomere subsecuriform to nearly digitiform; labium (
Figs. 8
, 
14
) with ligula deeply incised, ligular lobes narrowed, terminal palpomere subsecuriform to nearly digitiform; eyes large, coarsely facetted, ocular notch moderately sized; antenna (
Figs. 1
, 
17
) comprised of 10 antennomeres, capitate (
Fig. 1
); funicular antennomeres slightly expanded (
Fig. 16
) or substantially expanded (
Fig. 35
); capitulum long (
Fig. 23
) or short (
Fig. 22
). 
Thorax
: Pronotum (
Figs. 10, 11
) slightly transverse or quadrate, disc slightly convex, side margins with conspicuous lateral tubercle, dorsolateral carina incomplete, anteriorly extends beyond tubercle and confluent with pronotal hem posteriorly, prointercoxal process narrow (
Fig. 10
), not expanded distally; pronotal projections short, acuminate, not approximating prointercoxal process; elytron profusely sculptured with asetiferous punctures (
Fig. 20
), epipleural fold wide and tapered to elytral apex and gradually more oblique from anterior to posterior, elytral anterior margin not carinate; metathoracic wing as in 
Fig. 2
, wedge cell open; metendosternite (
Fig. 12
) with furcal lamina, furcal anterior plate large, triangular; profemora not swollen and without spines, tibial spur formula 1-2-2, tarsal pulvillar formula 3-3-3 (
Fig. 18
), ungues with basal denticle (
Fig. 19
). 
Abdomen
: Aedeagus shorter than length of abdomen, distal region of phallobase lobed, lateral lobes not fimbriate, tegmen reduced ventrally, submembranous, phallobasic struts confluent with phallobasic apodeme, phallobasic rod present, phallic plates wide and sometimes incised distally; spicular fork well-developed, spicular apodemes fused, interspicular plate long and linear. Ovipositor shorter than abdomen, laminae tripartite, laminal rod present.

